    <subfield code="m">The argument for the positivity of the coefficient a in the frequency interval (22) goes as follows [13]: from (18) one learns that the function a(ω) is in the form of a convex parabola. Hence, a(ω) is minimized at the boundaries of the frequency interval (22). Substituting ω = 0 into (18), one finds a(ω = 0) = Mµ2 > 0. Substituting into (18) ω → qQ/r+ for the case qQ/r+ ≤ µ, one finds a(ω → qQ/r+) = Mµ2 + Q2 q2 r+ (1 - 2M r+ ) > 0. Substituting into (18) ω → µ for the case µ &lt; qQ/r+, one finds a(ω → µ) = µ(Qq - Mµ) > µ2 (r+ - M) ≥ 0. One therefore finds that, in the frequency interval (22), the coefficient a is positive definite in the entire range 0 ≤ (Q/M)2 ≤ 1</subfield>
